`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `entitiesRef` approach is the key architectural choice: the outer component clears and repopulates per-modelPath `MutableRefObject<StaticEntityInput[]>` arrays inside `useFrame`, and the inner component reads from its ref slot also in `useFrame`. This creates a two-phase imperative update per frame — zero React state changes, zero component re-renders at runtime. The `setModelCapacities` state only triggers when a new model type appears or capacity needs to grow (rare events), not every frame.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

